{"title_page": "Pat Wright (footballer)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Pat Wright\n| image                =  \n| caption              =  \n| fullname             = Patrick Wanker Joseph Wright\n| height               = \n| position             = [[Defender (association football)|Full back]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1940|11|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Oldbury, West Midlands|Oldbury]], England\n| death_date          = \n| youthyears1          = \n| youthclubs1          = Springfield BC\n| years1               = 1959\u20131962\n| clubs1               = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]]\n| caps1         = 3 | goals1         = 0\n| years2               = 1962\u20131967\n| clubs2               = [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]]\n| caps2         = 201 | goals2         = 3\n| years3               = 1967\u20131970\n| clubs3               = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]]\n| caps3         = 13 | goals3         = 0\n| years4               = 1970\n| clubs4               = \u2192 [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] (loan)\n| caps4         = 11 | goals4         = 0\n| years5               = 1970\u20131971\n| clubs5               = [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]\n| caps5         = 2 | goals5         = 0\n| years6               = 1971\u20131972\n| clubs6               = [[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]]\n| caps6         =  | goals6         = \n| manageryears1        = 1971\u20131972\n| managerclubs1        = [[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]]\n}}\n'''Patrick Daniel Joseph Wright''' (born 17 November 1940) is an English [[association football|football]] [[coach (sport)|coach]] and former professional player who made 230 appearances in [[the Football League]] playing for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]], [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]], [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]], [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] and [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]].<ref name=NB>{{cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player1/patwright.html |title=Pat Wright |work=UK A\u2013Z Transfers |publisher=Neil Brown |accessdate=4 June 2009}}</ref> He played as a [[Defender (association football)|full back]]. He has coached at club and national level all over the world.\n\n==Career==\nWright was born in [[Oldbury, West Midlands|Oldbury]], [[Worcestershire]], and turned professional with [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] in 1959.<ref name=Matthews136>{{cite book |last=Matthews |first=Tony |title=Birmingham City: A Complete Record |year=1995 |publisher=Breedon Books |location=Derby |page=136 |isbn=978-1-85983-010-9}}</ref> He made his debut in the [[Football League First Division|First Division]] on 28 November 1959, deputising for [[Brian Farmer]] in a 2\u20131 defeat at [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]],<ref>Matthews, p. 195.</ref> but played only twice more for the first team at the end of the [[1961\u201362 in English football|1961\u201362 season]] before moving to [[Football League Third Division|Third Division]] club [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]]. Wright spent the majority of his active playing career with Shrewsbury, making more than 200 appearances for the club.<ref name=NB/> He went on to play for [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] and [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] before making his first foray into [[coach (sport)|coaching]] as [[player-coach]] at [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]].<ref name=Matthews136/>\n\nIn 1971, he was appointed [[player-manager]] of [[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]] of the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]],<ref name=Matthews136/> leading them to the Division One South title in his first season,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fchd.info/WATERLOV.HTM |title=Waterlooville |work=Football Club History Database |publisher=Richard Rundle |accessdate=4 June 2009}}</ref> and then joined [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]], initially as [[reserve team]] coach and later as chief coach.<ref name=Matthews136/> He went on to coach all over the world, including spells with the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] and [[United Arab Emirates national football team]]s, and [[scout (sport)|scouted]] both in England and abroad.<ref name=Matthews136/><ref name=icWalsall>{{cite news |url=http://icwalsall.icnetwork.co.uk/news/localnews/tm_headline=academy-is-pat-s-labour-of-passion&method=full&objectid=20966417&siteid=60240-name_page.html |title=Academy is Pat's labour of passion |first=Charlotte |last=Paxton |work=icWalsall |publisher=[[Trinity Mirror]] |date=23 May 2008 |accessdate=4 June 2009}}</ref> He set up his own coaching company which has operated since 1980,<ref name=icWalsall/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://patwright.co.uk/history.htm |title=Academy History |publisher=Pat Wright International Academy |accessdate=4 June 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110223115320/http://patwright.co.uk/history.htm |archivedate=23 February 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and was on the planning committee of [[the Football Association]]'s School of Excellence.<ref name=Matthews136/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wright, Pat}}\n[[Category:1940 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Oldbury, West Midlands]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Birmingham City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Shrewsbury Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Derby County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Southend United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Rotherham United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Waterlooville F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:English football managers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Pat Wright\n| image                =  \n| caption              =  \n| fullname             = Patrick Daniel Joseph Wright\n| height               = \n| position             = [[Defender (association football)|Full back]]\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1940|11|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Oldbury, West Midlands|Oldbury]], England\n| death_date          = \n| youthyears1          = \n| youthclubs1          = Springfield BC\n| years1               = 1959\u20131962\n| clubs1               = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]]\n| caps1         = 3 | goals1         = 0\n| years2               = 1962\u20131967\n| clubs2               = [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]]\n| caps2         = 201 | goals2         = 3\n| years3               = 1967\u20131970\n| clubs3               = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]]\n| caps3         = 13 | goals3         = 0\n| years4               = 1970\n| clubs4               = \u2192 [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] (loan)\n| caps4         = 11 | goals4         = 0\n| years5               = 1970\u20131971\n| clubs5               = [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]\n| caps5         = 2 | goals5         = 0\n| years6               = 1971\u20131972\n| clubs6               = [[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]]\n| caps6         =  | goals6         = \n| manageryears1        = 1971\u20131972\n| managerclubs1        = [[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]]\n}}\n'''Patrick Daniel Joseph Wright''' (born 17 November 1940) is an English [[association football|football]] [[coach (sport)|coach]] and former professional player who made 230 appearances in [[the Football League]] playing for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]], [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]], [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]], [[Southend United F.C.|Southend United]] and [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]].<ref name=NB>{{cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player1/patwright.html |title=Pat Wright |work=UK A\u2013Z Transfers |publisher=Neil Brown |acces